ÄThehunterwhodiscoversafoundlingistheactivepartyatthe
encounter.However,intheScottishromanceÑSirTristremÄwefind
anexampleinwhichtheactionislessone-sided.SirTristrem
arrivesinCornwalltofindMark'shuntsmenabouttocutupa
deerincorrectly;heshowsthemhowtodoitcorrectly,andis
takenintoMark'scourt.Tristremplaysamoreactivepartthan
thefoundlingsintheotherexamples.Intheotherromances,the
womanorchildtakesovertheroleofquarry-sheorheisfound
andtakenhome,theanimalbeingabandonedatthemomentofthe
foundling'sdiscovery.However,Tristremtakesovertheroleof
hunterandaltersthepracticeofthehuntersirrevocably.This
isagreaterimmediateeffectthananyofthefoundlingshave,
whoareinsteadadoptedandimbuedwiththeirfinder'sculture.
Tristremchangeskillingthedeerintohunting,hedefinesand
createsthehuntforMark'scourtandsoredefinesthesituation
inwhichhemetthehunters.Ofcourse,thisepisodeisfoundin
otherversionsoftheTristanlegend,andweshallreturntothis
specialrolelater.

Thecentralfeaturesofthemeetingmotifaretheprotagonist's
solitudeandtheconsequentchangeofdirectioninthenarrative.
Beforeameeting,theheroisalone,eitherbecausehehunts
aloneorbecausehehasbecomeseparatedfromhisfellows.Heis
effectivelyidle,havingnoinvolvementinanarrativesequence.
Thehuntingcharacterscanbedescribedintermsoftheirstatus
only-theEarlofToulouseê07,17Äisamiserablelover,Auferiousa
deceivedking,Lybeausanignorantboy.Theyhavethepotential
toholdourinterest,butneedintroducingintoanarrativein
ordertodoso;thehuntperformsthisfunction.Itisnotthen
surprisingthatmanymeetingscomenearthebeginningofthe
romances,astheydoinÑGenerydesÄ,ÑLybeausDesconusÄ,theÑRomans
ofPartenayÄ,ÑPartonopeofBloisÄ,theÑSowdonofBabylonÄandthe
ÑWeddyngeofSirGawenandDameRagnellê12,18Ä.Usuallythehunterisat
N017:002703230007
ÄTheEarlofToulouseishuntingwhenhemeetsamessengerwho
tellshimofhisbeloved'sneedforachampion.Heeventually
