Asintheverseromances,anoteofcensuremaybepresent-when
heshouldbeavailableincaseheisneeded,Tristramcannotbe
found.Thisperhapsforeshadowsthecriticismofthepositionof
huntinginTristram'sorderofprioritieslaterinMalory'swork.

Theubiquityoftheseductionorabductionmotifisapparentfrom
thenumberofcontrivedusesofit,allofwhichdependfortheir
plausibilityontheimmediateacceptabilityofthelikelihoodof
suchanevent.ThuswhenYvellliestothesultan,tellinghim
thatGenerydesplanstoabductClarionasduringthehunt,he
lendsGenerydes'ssupposedplotplausibilitybysituatingitina
hunt:theaudience(andperhapsthesultan)isaccustomedtosuch
occurrenceswithinromance,anditdoesnotsoundunlikely.Other
examplesinwhichcharactersexploitthefamiliarconventionof
abductionorseductionduringahuntarefoundinTheAvowingof
ArthurandKingHorn.InthefirstoftheseArthurtests
Bowdewynne'svownevertobejealousofhiswife.Hesends
