Theboar-hunt,then,whilefrequentlyservingthesamefunction
asthenarrativemotifsdiscussedaboveinhelpingtomovethe
plotalongtothenextstage,hastheadditionalimportant
functionofdevelopingaspectsofthehunter'scharacter.The
boar-hunterisaparagonofmilitaryprowess:heisbrave,
strong,dynamicyetalsoequippedwiththeusualcourtlygraces
ofthehunter,demonstratedinhisproperattentiontothe
treatmentofthecarcaseandtheframingofthecombatwithinthe
etiquetteofthecourtlyhunt.

Theboar-huntisnottheonlyhuntwhichmaybeusedtodefineor
refinethecharacterofaprotagonist.Itis,however,theonly
huntwhichpresentsanunambiguouscombinationofcourtlyand
militaryvirtues.Thedeer-hunt,thoughredolentofcourtliness,
could,asweshallnowsee,beusedasascathingcondemnationof
